President Joe Biden will have a phone call with President Vladimir Putin of Russia on December 30, 2021. The call will cover various topics, including upcoming diplomatic engagements with Russia. The Biden Administration has been actively engaging with European Allies and partners to coordinate a response to Russia's military build-up on the Ukraine border. President Biden has spoken with European leaders, and his administration has engaged with NATO, the EU, and the OSCE. They have also held consultations with counterparts from eastern flank countries, bilaterally and in the B9 format, as well as with Ukraine.